1 - Run ./setup-dev-env.sh
2 - Run bbb-akka-apps using ./run-dev.sh (inside the Docker)
3 - Run bbb-core-api using ./run-dev.sh (inside the Docker)
4 - You can access the new API in your browser (replace the domain) https://YOUR-DOMAIN/core-api/getMeetings?checksum=123
5 - Use API Mate to generate the checksum `bbb-conf -salt`

### Building the Docker Images

Each API service has its own Dockerfile following the naming convention `Dockerfile-{service}` where `service` is substituted with the
API name. As an example, to build the Docker image for the meeting API use the following commands:
```
go mod vendor
docker build -f Dockerfile-meeting -t imdt/bigbluebutton-api-meeting:latest .
```